   I have two kids playing hockey. One was in 8U and the other in 10U. The one that was in 8U wasn't performing to his potential and skill and was otherwise bored watching his teammates be puck hogs on a small congested surface. When his brothers 10U team was short players I had him dress and play up. There was some concern based on his performance in 8U, but I knew he could skate. Throw in parents saying "Don't pass it to your (less skilled) line mates... it's a waste of the puck... it's like passing it to the other team", and you've got a recipe for a break-away relay.  (the kid of the Dad who actually instructed his kid this within ear shot of my kid got 34 goals and 3 assists the following summer in his 4 on 4 league - by minor midget, the boy was a layman single A player - far too predictable to get the job done after the D-men had learned to skate well) ', b'My kids had passed the mite level when this was coming out.
